Overview
*********
The ICOOOLPS workshop series brings together researchers and practitioners=
=20
working in the field of OO languages implementation and optimization.=20
ICOOOLPS key goal is to identify current and emerging issues relating to=20
the efficient implementation, compilation and optimization of such language=
s,=20
and outlining future challenges and research directions.
Topics of interest for ICOOOLPS include, but are not limited to: implementa=
tion=20
of fundamental OO and OO-like features (e.g. inheritance, parametric types,=
=20
memory management, objects, prototypes), runtime systems (e.g. compilers,=20
linkers, virtual machines, garbage collectors), optimizations (e.g. static =
or=20
dynamic analyses, adaptive virtual machines), resource constraints (e.g. ti=
me=20
for real-time systems, space or low-power for embedded systems) and relevan=
t=20
choices and tradeoffs (e.g. constant time vs. non-constant time mechanisms,=
=20
separate compilation vs. global compilation, dynamic loading vs. global=20
linking, dynamic checking vs. proof-carrying code...).


